==Events== * [[480]] &ndash; [[Odoacer]], first [[King of Italy]], occupies [[Dalmatia]]. He later establishes his political power with the co-operation of the [[Roman Senate]]. * [[536]] &ndash; [[Gothic War (535–554)|Gothic War]]: The Byzantine general [[Belisarius]] enters Rome unopposed; the [[Goths|Gothic]] garrison flee the capital. * [[730]] &ndash; [[Battle of Marj Ardabil]]: The [[Khazars]] annihilate an [[Umayyad]] army and kill its commander, [[al-Jarrah ibn Abdallah al-Hakami|Al-Jarrah Ibn Abdallah Al-Hakami]]. *[[1425]] &ndash; The [[Old University of Leuven|Catholic University of Leuven]] is founded. *[[1531]] &ndash; [[Our Lady of Guadalupe|The Virgin of Guadalupe]] first appears to [[Juan Diego]] at [[Tepeyac|Tepeyac, Mexico City]]. *[[1688]] &ndash; [[Glorious Revolution]]: Williamite forces defeat Jacobites at [[Battle of Reading (1688)|Battle of Reading]], forcing flight of [[James II]] from the country. *[[1775]] &ndash; [[American Revolutionary War]]: British troops lose the [[Battle of Great Bridge]], and leave [[Virginia]] soon afterward. *[[1793]] &ndash; New York City's first daily [[newspaper]], the ''American Minerva'', is established by [[Noah Webster]]. *[[1824]] &ndash; Patriot forces led by General [[Antonio José de Sucre]] defeat a Royalist army in the [[Battle of Ayacucho]], putting an end to the [[Peruvian War of Independence]]. *[[1835]] &ndash; [[Texas Revolution]]: The [[Texian Army]] captures [[San Antonio, Texas]]. *[[1851]] &ndash; The first [[YMCA]] in North America is established in [[Montreal]]. *[[1856]] &ndash; The [[Iran]]ian city of [[Bushehr]] surrenders to occupying British forces. *[[1861]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: The [[Joint Committee on the Conduct of the War]] is established by the [[Congress of the United States|U.S. Congress]]. *[[1868]] &ndash; The first [[traffic light]]s are installed, outside the [[Palace of Westminster]] in London. Resembling [[railway signal]]s, they use [[Railway semaphore signal|semaphore]] arms and are illuminated at night by red and green [[gas lamp]]s. *[[1872]] &ndash; In [[Louisiana]], [[P. B. S. Pinchback]] becomes the first [[African-American]] governor of a U.S. state. *[[1892]] &ndash; English football club [[Newcastle United]] is founded. *[[1897]] &ndash; Activist [[Marguerite Durand]] founds the [[feminist]] daily newspaper ''[[La Fronde (newspaper)|La Fronde]]'' in Paris. *[[1905]] &ndash; In France, the [[1905 French law on the Separation of the Churches and the State|law separating church and state]] is passed. *[[1911]] &ndash; A [[Cross Mountain Mine disaster|mine explosion]] near [[Briceville, Tennessee]], kills 84 miners despite rescue efforts led by the [[United States Bureau of Mines]]. *[[1917]] &ndash; [[World War I]]: Field Marshal [[Edmund Allenby, 1st Viscount Allenby|Allenby]] captures [[Battle of Jerusalem|Jerusalem]], [[History of Palestine#Ottoman era|Palestine]]. *[[1922]] &ndash; [[Gabriel Narutowicz]] is elected the first president of Poland. *[[1931]] &ndash; The [[Constituent Cortes]] approves a [[Spanish Constitution of 1931|constitution]] which establishes the [[Second Spanish Republic]]. *[[1935]] &ndash; [[December 9th Movement|Student protests]] in Beiping (now Beijing)'s Tiananmen Square, dispersed by [[Kuomintang|government]]. *[[1935]] &ndash; [[Walter Liggett]], American newspaper editor and muckraker, is killed in a gangland murder. * 1935 &ndash; The [[Downtown Athletic Club|Downtown Athletic Club Trophy]], later renamed the [[Heisman Trophy]], is awarded for the first time. The winner is halfback [[Jay Berwanger]] of the [[University of Chicago]]. *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Second Sino-Japanese War]]: [[Battle of Nanking]]: [[Empire of Japan|Japanese]] troops under the command of Lt. Gen. [[Asaka Yasuhiko]] launch an assault on the [[Republic of China (1912–49)|Chinese]] city of [[Nanjing]] (Nanking). *[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Operation Compass]]: British and Indian troops under the command of Major-General [[Richard O'Connor]] [[Battle of Sidi Barrani|attack]] [[Military history of Italy during World War II|Italian]] forces near [[Sidi Barrani]] in [[Egypt]]. *[[1941]] &ndash; World War II: [[Republic of China (1912–49)|China]], [[Cuba]], [[Guatemala]], and [[Commonwealth of the Philippines|the Philippine Commonwealth]] declare war on [[Nazi Germany|Germany]] and [[Empire of Japan|Japan]]. * 1941 &ndash; World War II: The American [[19th Operations Group|19th Bombardment Group]] attacks Japanese ships off the coast of [[Vigan]], [[Luzon]]. *[[1946]] &ndash; The "[[Subsequent Nuremberg trials]]" begin with the "[[Doctors' trial]]", prosecuting physicians and officers alleged to be involved in [[Nazi human experimentation]] and [[Action T4|mass murder under the guise of euthanasia]]. * 1946 &ndash; The [[Constituent Assembly of India]] meets for the first time to write the [[Constitution of India]]. *[[1948]] &ndash; The [[Genocide Convention]] is adopted. *[[1950]] &ndash; [[Cold War]]: [[Harry Gold]] is sentenced to 30 years in jail for helping [[Klaus Fuchs]] pass information about the [[Manhattan Project]] to the [[Soviet Union]]. His testimony is later instrumental in the prosecution of [[Julius and Ethel Rosenberg]]. *[[1953]] &ndash; [[Second Red Scare|Red Scare]]: [[General Electric]] announces that all [[communist]] employees will be discharged from the company. *[[1956]] &ndash; [[Trans-Canada Air Lines Flight 810]], a [[Canadair North Star]], crashes near [[Hope, British Columbia]], Canada, killing all 62 people on board. *[[1958]] &ndash; The [[John Birch Society]] is founded in the United States. *[[1960]] &ndash; The first episode of ''[[Coronation Street]]'', the world's longest-running television [[soap opera]], is broadcast in the United Kingdom. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Tanganyika]] becomes independent from Britain. *[[1962]] &ndash; The [[Petrified Forest National Park]] is established in [[Arizona]]. *[[1965]] &ndash; [[Kecksburg UFO incident]]: A fireball is seen from Michigan to Pennsylvania; witnesses report something crashing in the woods near Pittsburgh. * 1965 &ndash; ''[[A Charlie Brown Christmas]]'', first in a series of ''[[Peanuts]]'' television specials, debuts on [[CBS]]. *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Douglas Engelbart]] gave what became known as "[[The Mother of All Demos]]", publicly debuting the [[computer mouse]], [[hypertext]], and the bit-mapped [[graphical user interface]] using the [[NLS (computer system)|oN-Line System (NLS)]]. *[[1969]] &ndash; U.S. Secretary of State [[William P. Rogers]] proposes [[Rogers Plan|his plan]] for a ceasefire in the [[War of Attrition]]; Egypt and Jordan accept it over the objections of the [[Palestine Liberation Organization|PLO]], which leads to [[Black September in Jordan|civil war in Jordan]] in September 1970. * 1971 &ndash; [[Indo-Pakistani War of 1971|Indo-Pakistani War]]: The [[Indian Air Force]] executes [[Meghna Heli Bridge|an airdrop]] of [[Indian Army]] units, bypassing Pakistani defences. *[[1973]] &ndash; British and Irish authorities sign the [[Sunningdale Agreement]] in an attempt to establish a power-sharing [[Northern Ireland Executive (1974)|Northern Ireland Executive]] and a cross-border [[Council of Ireland]]. *[[1979]] &ndash; The eradication of the [[smallpox]] [[virus]] is certified, making smallpox the first of only two diseases that have been driven to extinction ([[rinderpest]] in 2011 being the other). *[[1987]] &ndash; [[Israeli–Palestinian conflict]]: The [[First Intifada]] begins in the [[Gaza Strip]] and [[West Bank]]. *[[1988]] &ndash; The [[Michael Hughes Bridge]] in [[Sligo]], Ireland, is officially opened. *[[1992]] &ndash; American troops land in [[Somalia]] for [[Unified Task Force|Operation Restore Hope]]. *[[1996]] &ndash; [[Topfreedom in Canada#Gwen Jacob|Gwen Jacob is acquitted]] of committing an indecent act, giving women the right to be topfree in Ontario, Canada. *[[2003]] &ndash; A [[2003 Red Square bombing|blast]] in the center of Moscow kills six people and wounds several more. *[[2008]] &ndash; The [[Governor of Illinois]], [[Rod Blagojevich]], is arrested by federal officials for crimes including attempting to sell the [[United States Senate|U.S. Senate]] seat being vacated by [[President-elect of the United States|President-elect]] [[Barack Obama]]. *[[2012]] &ndash; A [[2012 Mexico Learjet 25 crash|plane crash]] in Mexico kills seven people.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.today.com/popculture/u-s-mexican-singer-jenni-rivera-feared-dead-plane-crash-wbna50139715 |title=U.S.-Mexican singer Jenni Rivera feared dead in plane crash |date= 10 December 2012|accessdate=25 January 2019 |work=[[NBC News]] |agency=[[Reuters]]}}</ref> *[[2013]] &ndash; At least seven are dead and 63 are injured following a [[2013 Bintaro train crash|train accident]] near Bintaro, [[Indonesia]]. *[[2015]] &ndash; The start of the thirty-sixth [[Gulf Cooperation Council|GCC]] summit in [[Riyadh]] business. *[[2016]] &ndash; [[President of South Korea|President]] [[Park Geun-hye]] of [[South Korea]] is [[Impeachment of Park Geun-hye|impeached]] by the country's [[National Assembly (South Korea)|National Assembly]] in response to a [[2016 South Korean political scandal|major political scandal]]. [[Prime Minister of South Korea|Prime Minister]] [[Hwang Kyo-ahn]] becomes Acting President, later declining to run for a full term. * 2016 &ndash; At least 57 people are killed and a further 177 injured when two schoolgirl suicide bombers attack a market area in [[Madagali]], Northeastern Nigeria in the [[Madagali suicide bombings]]. *[[2017]] &ndash; The [[Marriage Amendment (Definition and Religious Freedoms) Bill 2017|Marriage Amendment Bill]] receives royal assent and comes into effect, making [[Australia]] the 26th country to legalize [[same-sex marriage]]. *[[2019]] &ndash; A volcano on [[Whakaari / White Island|White Island]], [[New Zealand]], kills at least 18 people after it [[2019 Whakaari / White Island eruption|erupts]].<ref>{{Cite news|url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-50715047|title= New Zealand volcano: 'No sign of life' after White Island eruption|date=2019-12-09|work=BBC|access-date=2019-12-09|language=en}}</ref>
